title.label: A rare treasure among mobile games.

content.label: Part Time UFO is hands down the best mobile game I’ve ever played. The gameplay while simple, is incredibly fun. Each level has certain stipulations for extra points, and figuring out how to achieve them is very satisfying. What’s more is that there are no, I repeat, NO micro transactions! Do you have any idea how rare that is for the mobile game industry?? It’s almost unheard of! The game features a shop where you can spend in-game currency, and beating levels gives you more than a generous amount. Hal Laboratories knocked it out of the park with this gem. I highly recommend this game!

Part time UFO is a physics based puzzle game where you are a cute little UFO who starts taking part time labor jobs to make ends meet.  Each job has a main objective as well as 3 challenge objectives which will net you medals that are used to unlock new levels.  It gets harder as you progress and you can spend the in game money you earn on costumes which give different bonuses and change the behavior of the controls.  I highly recommend this game to anybody.

Part Time UFO is the most delightful game I’ve seen on iOS in years. There’s something very WarioWare about it, but with more consistency and less pressure. It’s absolutely adorbs, from the character design, to the background details, to the way the UFO starts singing along with the soundtrack. It’s easy to get the hang of and fairly simple to beat, but the optional 100% challenges offer plenty of difficulty. If you don’t love this game, there may be something very wrong with you.
